That it is more desirable for the fiscal interests that the office of entry
                        and dispatch of merchandise destined for the interior consumption of the
                        Republic should be at Yzabal;

That by decree No. 278 of June 14, 1882, the opening of Livingston as a free
                        port and of deposit was ordered in attention to the special circumstances of
                        that period;
